Basic size
```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}]
```

Grid - half size, except one which is explicit
```
Grid[{
    {
        ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}],
        ContourPlot[{x^2+y^2 == 1, x^2-y^2==0.5} , {x,-2,2},{y,-2,2}]
    },
    {
        ContourPlot[{x^2+y^2 == 1, x^2-y^2==0.5} , {x,-2,2},{y,-2,2}],
        ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}, ImageSize->100]
    }
}]
```

Basic size again

```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}]
```

Row - quarter size
```
Row[{
    ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}],
    ContourPlot[{x^2+y^2 == 1, x^2-y^2==0.5} , {x,-2,2},{y,-2,2}]
}]
```

